<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-07-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-07-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="420" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Barlow</persName>,
                                    United States marshal, to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>, Secretary of State.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi></placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-07-15"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 15, 1809</date>.</dateline>
                            <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>:</p>
                            <p>Authorization received. Some two hundred persons are on Gardner’s
                                Island. They refuse to leave on the request of my officers and the
                                cutter. They have robbed the light-house keeper. I must send down a
                                sufficient force to oblige them to leave. I shall act very
                                discreetly. If I cannot get enough marines may I ask for a few
                                troops?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>FRANCIS C. BARLOW,<lb/><hi rend="italic">United States
                                        Marshal.</hi></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>